results.name: Self-inverse signature permutation of a Catalan bijection: row 183 of A089840.
comment: This bijection of binary trees swaps the left and right subtree of a binary tree, but ONLY if either of them is empty. If both the left and right hand side tree is nonempty, fixes the tree.
This automorphism demonstrates that not every clause in clause-representations of A089840 is equal to some (minimally represented) element of Thompson's group V.
reference: J. W. Cannon, W. J. Floyd and W. R. Parry, Introductory notes on Richard Thompson's groups, L'Enseignement Mathematique, Vol. 42 (1996), pp. 215--256.
link: A. Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..2055
